Senior German officials are set to travel to the U.S. 'shortly' for talks about allegations the NSA bugged Angela Merkel's phone.

The heads of Germany's foreign and domestic intelligence agencies will participate in high-level discussions with the White House and National Security Agency, government spokesman Georg Streiter said.

He did not give a specific date for the trip, saying it was being arranged on 'relatively short notice'.

