The International Covenant on Political and Civil Rights was written in 1966 and came into force in 1976, long before the internet was invented.

Article 17, says 'no one shall be subjected to arbitrary or unlawful interference with his privacy, family, home or correspondence, nor to unlawful attacks on his honor and reputation.'

